WH> .Yes, but sending encrypted information over the airwaves is illegal
  > .under some circumstances, does anyone know when exactly?

Virtually all the time in the Amateur Radio service.  Encryption or
scrambling is allowable in the Private Land Mobile Radio Services,
except when broadcasting a station identification.

